\details{
Provides methods for placing, cancelling, and querying spot orders on KuCoin.
All order operations use the HF (High-Frequency) trading endpoints.
Inherits from \link{KucoinBase}.
\subsection{Purpose and Scope}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Order Placement}: Place single or batch limit/market orders with full parameter control.
\item \strong{Order Testing}: Validate order parameters without execution via the test endpoint.
\item \strong{Order Cancellation}: Cancel by order ID, client OID, partially, by symbol, or all at once.
\item \strong{Order Queries}: Retrieve order details, open orders, closed orders, fills, and symbols with activity.
}
}

\subsection{Usage}{

All methods require authentication (valid API key, secret, passphrase).
The \code{KucoinTrading} class consolidates functionality previously split across
\code{KucoinSpotAddOrder}, \code{KucoinSpotCancelOrder}, and \code{KucoinSpotGetOrder}.
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/orders/add-order}{KuCoin Spot Trading Orders}
}

